    <title><media type="image" src="figures/modem-manager-gui-logo.png"/>Modem Manager GUI manual</title>
    
    <p>
    <app>Modem Manager GUI</app> is a graphical frontend for the ModemManager daemon
    which is able to control specific modem functions.
    </p>
    
    <p>
    You can use <app>Modem Manager GUI</app> for the following tasks:
    </p>
    
    <list>
        <item>
            <p>Create and control mobile broadband connections</p>
        </item>
        <item>
            <p>Send and receive SMS messages and store messages in database</p>
       </item>
       <item>
            <p>Initiate USSD requests and read answers (also using interactive sessions)</p>
       </item>
       <item>
            <p>View device information: operator name, device mode, IMEI, IMSI, signal level</p>
       </item>
       <item>
            <p>Scan available mobile networks</p>
       </item>
       <item>
            <p>View mobile traffic statistics and set limits</p>
       </item>
    </list>
    
